name: olympic-coast-national-marine-sanctuary-mos111-0205-side-scan-sonar-mosaic-of-survey-are-0205
notes: This side scan sonar imagery of the sea floor (40-100 m water depths) was mosaiced from acoustic data collected in 2002 aboard the NOAA ship McArthur. A Klein System 3000 dual frequency side scan system was used for geophysical surveying, using only the100Khz data to create the mosaic. Isis Sonar (Triton Imaging International) was used to log the digital sonar packets. Sonar data were captured using the 150m range scale setting.
